> Our first ever mashed potato bowl is here, and why didn't we think of it sooner? Huge props to T-Pain's culinary prowess—you're truly an inspiration! This classic pairing of chicken and potatoes brings an exciting twist to the table: The chicken is dredged in a sweet, smoky, and spicy flour mixture before it's sizzled to golden, juicy perfection. You'll nestle it into buttery mashed potatoes along with tender-crisp green beans. Smother it all with lots of rich, creamy gravy (and a drizzle of hot sauce if you like, you do you!).

== Potatoes and Green Beans ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. (TIP: For a smoother texture, peel potatoes first.) Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid (1 cup for 4 servings), then drain. Return potatoes to #pot{} and cover to keep warm.

While potatoes cook, toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender and browned, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Chicken ==

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

In a #shallow dish{}, combine @Brown Sugar Bourbon Seasoning{10.8%g}, half the @Flour{1%tablespoon}, half the @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, and as much @Chili Powder{1%teaspoon} as you like. Press chicken into flour mixture to evenly coat.

> We used ½ tsp chili powder; 1 tsp for 4 servings. Add more if you like it extra-spicy!

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

== Gravy ==

Return pan used for chicken to medium heat and add @Butter{1%tablespoon}. Once butter has melted, add remaining flour and cook, whisking constantly, until a loose paste forms, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2} and 1/3 cup water (2/3 cup for 4); cook, whisking constantly, until gravy has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat and whisk in @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

To pot with potatoes, add @Butter{1%tablespoon} and remaining garlic powder.

Mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Taste and season with salt and pepper if necessary.

== Assembly ==

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide mashed potatoes between bowls. Top with chicken and green beans in separate sections; drizzle everything with gravy.

> Add a drizzle of your favorite hot sauce for an extra kick!

Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.